{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 / T11 (Data-migration & backfill safety): PASS — no findings.\n\nT11 is an overlay that applies when a plan changes a persisted format or backfills data. Verified against the codebase that `compiled_state` is an in-memory projection rebuilt by replaying the event log through the reducer (`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:515` `process_snapshot` simply restores fields from `compiled_state`; `replay_events` rebuilds state on the normal reduce/restore path). There is NO SQL schema, DDL, or large-table backfill transaction — so the heavy-DDL hazards (blocking lock, batching, dual-write cutover window) do not structurally apply; ANTI-FP: this is an event-sourced reseed, not a persisted-row backfill.\n\nThe plan's own text affirmatively satisfies every load-bearing dimension for this lazy per-ticket reseed:\n- (a) Online / no blocking DDL: new field/event \"preserved-and-ignored by older clones (forward-compatible rollout)\" — additive, no downtime.\n- (b) Batching/scale: \"Per-ticket ref cardinality is small (tens)\"; seeding runs on the normal reduce path, per ticket — no giant transaction.\n- (c) Resumable/idempotent: seeds only \"On the FIRST reduce/restore where managed_refs is absent\" and is \"STRICTLY MONOTONIC\" thereafter — re-runnable without double-apply (AC2).\n- (d) Dual-write window: a lazy read-path reseed has no separate backfill-vs-cutover window; during any absence the gate \"defaults to EMPTY => returns False (additive-only: no remove, no clobber)\" — no lost writes.\n- (e) Rollback / no data loss: explicit back-out (\"disabling the fold leaves the gate a safe no-op\"); seeding \"is safe in both directions\" and never clobbers Jira-only refs; partial failure degrades additive-only.\n\nAffirmations: T11(a) online/expand-contract-equivalent, T11(b) batching/scale, T11(c) resumability/idempotency, T11(d) dual-write window, T11(e) rollback/no-data-loss — all satisfied by the plan text. Clean chunk (empty findings) for T11."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782538278420331001,"uuid":"075477bf-32fc-4105-ae19-f18296f170d1"}